WEBVTT

00:11:56.665 --> 00:12:00.562
which is that we should be
more humble as a species,

00:12:00.586 --> 00:12:03.197
you know, "Yes, we have
our extraordinary skills,

00:12:03.221 --> 00:12:06.966
but frankly, every species
has its extraordinary skills.

00:12:06.990 --> 00:12:10.506
We're good at language,
and we can build these amazing things,

00:12:10.530 --> 00:12:14.910
but, you know, an elephant has
thousands of muscles in its trunk,

00:12:14.934 --> 00:12:18.164
and the exquisite way
in which it can manipulate that --

00:12:18.188 --> 00:12:19.903
that's like nothing else we can do.

00:12:19.927 --> 00:12:23.338
Ants and bees have these
extraordinary social lives ...

00:12:23.362 --> 00:12:26.966
Every species is, actually,
in a very real sense,

00:12:26.990 --> 00:12:28.553
equally evolved as we are,

00:12:28.577 --> 00:12:31.188
because it's been evolving
for exactly as long